Jenna Etheridge, News24Cape Town - A bag containing various arms and explosives was uncovered in a cemetery in Kleinvlei, Cape Town, Western Cape police said on Wednesday.The bag was found buried in Welmoed cemetery on Tuesday night, Lieutenant-Colonel Andre Traut said.It contained a hunting rifle with a telescope, a silencer, a smoke grenade, stun grenade, seven detonators, three R4 rifle magazines and various rounds of ammunition.Two blasting caps were wrapped in a Zimbabwean newspaper. Some of the items were known to be used in ATM explosions.No one had yet been arrested.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.